Which of the following shows a valid Bash function called sayHello?
A)  function sayHello() { echo "hello"; }
B)  function sayHello{}
C)  function sayHello() { echo Hello }
D)  function sayHello() { echo Hello } ;
A
A. The correct syntax is as shown. Note that a semicolon is required when the commandsare included on one line, as shown in the correct answer.
